main event: A military observer in Caracas, Venezuela spotted a pinkish, grapefruitSized object moving at high speed on December 5, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be the size of a grapefruit and was pinkish in color.
The object moved at a speed that was about 3 times faster than a normal satellite.
The observer noted that the object had no blinking lights or body markings, and made no sound.
The object was visible for about 1 minute, traveling in a straight path about 50 degrees above the horizon.
The observer initially thought the object was a normal satellite, but the size and speed of the object may have invalidated that conclusion.
